entries.meaning: (transitive) To strip (a tree, etc.) of bark.

description: Middle French desbarquer, from des- + barque.

verbs.description: disbark (third-person singular simple present disbarks, present participle disbarking, simple past and past participle disbarked)

examples: The ship we moor on these obscure abodes; Disbark the sheep, an offering to the gods
